---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Ordinal from "../components/Ordinal.astro";
---

<Base
  title="FCWS"
  description="8th International Workshop on Flame Chemistry — Kyoto, Japan, 25–26 July 2026"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">
        <span class="edition-badge"><Ordinal n={8} /> Edition</span>
        <span class="edition-year">Kyoto, Japan &middot; 2026</span>
      </div>
      <h1>International Workshop<br/>on Flame Chemistry</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Advancing combustion chemistry through experiment, theory, and kinetics modeling
      </p>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <div class="hero-meta-item">
          <span class="hero-meta-label">Date</span>
          <span class="hero-meta-value">25–26 July 2026</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-meta-item">
          <span class="hero-meta-label">Venue</span>
          <span class="hero-meta-value">Doshisha University, Kyoto</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-meta-item">
          <span class="hero-meta-label">Part of</span>
          <span class="hero-meta-value"><Ordinal n={41} /> ISOC Pre-Workshops</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/registration" class="btn btn-primary">Register</a>
        <a href="/program" class="btn btn-ghost">View Program</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key facts strip -->
  <div class="facts-strip">
    <div class="facts-strip-inner">
      <div class="fact-item">
        <div class="fact-label">Early Bird Deadline</div>
        <div class="fact-value">21 June 2026</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <div class="fact-label">Regular Deadline</div>
        <div class="fact-value">12 July 2026</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <div class="fact-label">Registration</div>
        <div class="fact-value">Via Combustion Institute</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <div class="fact-label">Format</div>
        <div class="fact-value">Two full days + joint RCM session</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <div class="content-body">
    <div class="content-cols">

      <!-- Left: main text -->
      <div>
        <div class="section-rule">
          <h2>About the Workshop</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          The International Workshop on Flame Chemistry (FCWS) aims to advance understanding
          of combustion chemistry through close interaction between experiments, theory, and
          chemical kinetics modeling — particularly in the context of the global energy transition.
        </p>
        <p>
          FCWS provides a focused forum to identify key scientific challenges, foster
          interdisciplinary collaboration, and promote coordinated strategies toward predictive
          combustion chemistry models. The workshop addresses fundamental and applied aspects
          of flame chemistry underlying flame propagation, ignition, pollutant formation, and
          combustion system performance.
        </p>
        <p>
          Building on outcomes from previous editions, discussions at the <Ordinal n={8} /> FCWS will be
          guided by a recent perspective paper arising from the <Ordinal n={7} /> FCWS in Milan (2024),
          published in <em>Combustion and Flame</em>:
        </p>

        <div class="paper-card">
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.combustflame.2026.114863" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="border:none; flex-shrink:0;">
            <img src="/images/combustion-flame-logo.jpg" alt="Combustion and Flame journal cover" class="paper-cover" />
          </a>
          <div class="paper-info">
            <p class="paper-title">
              "Flame Chemistry Workshop: a perspective on challenges and strategic actions
              in combustion experiments and chemical kinetics modeling"
            </p>
            <p class="paper-authors">
              B. Rotavera, L. Cai, F. Zhang, A. Comandini, N. Hansen,
              S.J. Klippenstein, B. Yang, M. Pelucchi
            </p>
            <p class="paper-ref">
              <em>Combustion and Flame</em>, Vol. 286, April 2026, Article 114863
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.combustflame.2026.114863"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="paper-doi"
            >
              doi:10.1016/j.combustflame.2026.114863 →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-rule" style="margin-top: 2.75rem;">
          <h2>Focus Areas — <Ordinal n={8} /> FCWS</h2>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Sustainable fuels combustion</li>
          <li>Advanced diagnostics</li>
          <li>Plasma-assisted combustion</li>
          <li>AI, automation, and benchmarking in theoretical kinetics</li>
          <li>Chemical kinetics mechanism development</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-rule" style="margin-top: 2.75rem;">
          <h2>History</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          The workshop was founded in 2012 by <strong>Yiguang Ju</strong> (Princeton University)
          and <strong>Hai Wang</strong> (Stanford University) with the mission to assemble
          leading experts in combustion chemistry, flame diagnostics, and kinetic modeling to
          identify critical knowledge gaps and chart pathways toward predictive high-pressure
          flame chemistry.
        </p>
        <p>
          Since its inaugural edition at Warsaw University of Technology, the workshop has
          grown into a biennial community event held as a satellite of the International
          Symposium on Combustion, spanning Warsaw (2012), San Francisco (2014), Seoul (2016),
          Dublin (2018), Adelaide (2020, held online), Vancouver (2022), and Milan (2024). Each edition has
          produced structured research recommendations and fostered long-term collaborative
          initiatives across the combustion chemistry community.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/archive">View all past editions →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: sidebar -->
      <aside>
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h4>Important Dates</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Poster abstract deadline<br/><strong>12 June 2026</strong></li>
            <li>Early bird registration until<br/><strong>21 June 2026</strong></li>
            <li>Regular registration until<br/><strong>12 July 2026</strong></li>
            <li>Workshop<br/><strong>25–26 July 2026</strong></li>
            <li><Ordinal n={41} /> ISOC<br/><strong>26–31 July 2026</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h4>Joint Session</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Half-morning session co-organized with the <strong>RCM Workshop</strong>, led by Scott Goldsborough, Argonne National Laboratory, USA, on common challenges and best practices for community-driven efforts.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>


        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h4>Organised under</h4>
          <a href="https://www.combustioninstitute.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="border:none; display:inline-block; margin-top:0.4rem;">
            <img
              src="/images/ci-logo.png"
              alt="The Combustion Institute"
              width="110"
              style="opacity:0.75; transition: opacity 0.2s;"
              onmouseover="this.style.opacity='1'"
              onmouseout="this.style.opacity='0.75'"
            />
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
.paper-card {
  border-left: 3px solid var(--blue);
  background: var(--bg-tinted);
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  gap: 1.25rem;
  align-items: flex-start;
}

.paper-cover {
  width: 64px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

.paper-info { flex: 1; }

.paper-title {
  font-style: italic;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--ink);
  margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  line-height: 1.45;
}

.paper-authors {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}

.paper-ref {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}

.paper-doi {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--blue);
  border-bottom-color: transparent;
}
.paper-doi:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--blue); }

.founders {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}

.founder {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.75rem;
}

.founder img {
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center 20%;
  border-radius: 50%;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  filter: grayscale(20%);
  border: 2px solid var(--rule);
}

.founder div {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.1rem;
}

.founder strong {
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  color: var(--ink);
}

.founder span {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--ink-muted);
}
</style>
